{
  "texts": [
    "Given a graph G (V, X, A), where V is a set containing N nodes, denoted as",
    ", N represents the total number of nodes, and X is the node feature matrix, whose dimensionality is N × d, which represents that each node has d -dimen- sional features.",
    "The feature vector of the node v i is denoted as x i and is located in the i -th row of X.",
    "A is the adjacency matrix with dimension N × N, which is used to characterize the connectivity between nodes.",
    "If there is an edge between node v i and node v j, A i,j = 1, conversely, if there is no direct connection, A i,j = 0."
  ]
}